# Top-level (direct) dependencies ONLY.
#
# This is the file you edit by hand. Every transitive dependency and the exact
# pinned versions are generated into requirements.txt by pip-compile:
#
#     pip-compile                  # regenerate requirements.txt
#     pip-compile -U               # + upgrade everything to latest allowed
#     pip-compile -P requests      # + upgrade just one package
#
# Leave versions unconstrained for most packages; add a constraint (e.g.
# "requests>=2.31") only for large/critical packages that are harder to upgrade.
# See the README section "Keeping dependencies up to date".
#
# We deliberately keep a SINGLE requirements file (runtime + test tooling), as
# recommended in "Boost Your Django DX": the overhead of extra dev/prod files
# outweighs the small cost of a couple of test-only packages.

# Runtime
beautifulsoup4
requests

# Tests
pytest
requests-mock
